### Step 3: Fix connector line / step alignment in HowItWorks

File: `src/components/LandingPage/HowItWorks/index.tsx`

- [x] Replace the fixed `h-12` connector line between pipeline steps with
      a flex-based approach: make the connector line fill the remaining
      vertical space of its parent rather than using a hardcoded height.
      The parent `<div>` for each node already uses `flex flex-col
      items-center`. Change the connector `<div>` from `w-px h-12` to
      `w-px flex-1` (or `w-px grow`) so it stretches to match however
      tall the adjacent text content is.
- [x] Remove `pb-10` from the text container (the `<div>` at line 62) and
      replace it with a consistent bottom margin or gap that coordinates
      with the connector. The goal: the connector line always spans from
      one step circle to the next regardless of annotation text length,
      and no annotation text visually overflows past the connector on
      any viewport width.
- [x] Verify at 375px that long annotation text (e.g., the spec-writer
      and researcher annotations are the longest) does not extend below
      the connector line.

Spec trace: The spec requires six named agents shown as vertical nodes
with one-sentence annotations. The pipeline visualization must work at
all three audit widths. Playbook responsive rule: use Tailwind responsive
prefixes, not runtime calculation.

