### Step 4: Increase contrast on VsRulesPacks comparison cards

File: `src/components/LandingPage/VsRulesPacks/index.tsx`

- [x] Widen the visual gap between the "Rules packs" card and the "AIDE"
      card. Current difference is subtle (`border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900/30`
      vs `border-zinc-700 bg-zinc-900/50`). Change the AIDE card to use
      a more visible treatment — raise the border to `border-zinc-600` and
      the background to `bg-zinc-900/70` (or a similarly distinct step up).
      The Rules packs card should feel muted/recessed; the AIDE card should
      feel elevated/highlighted.
- [x] Fix the `—` and `+` marker contrast. Change the `—` markers from
      `text-zinc-600` to `text-zinc-500` and the `+` markers from
      `text-zinc-500` to `text-zinc-400` (or `text-emerald-500` /
      `text-emerald-400` for a subtle positive signal — implementor
      judgment call, but the color must be readable against its
      background). The markers are semantic — they communicate "bad" vs
      "good" — and must be legible without squinting.

Spec trace: Strategy beat 4 requires a dedicated section naming rules
packs as the nearest-neighbor category and describing specific mechanical
differences. The comparison only works if the two sides are visually
distinguishable. The spec's Bad Examples section warns against patterns
that look acceptable in isolation but fail their communicative purpose.

