### Step 5: Improve mobile stacked comparison cards

File: `src/components/LandingPage/VsRulesPacks/index.tsx`

- [x] When the grid collapses to single column at `<sm`, add explicit
      visual hierarchy to distinguish the two stacked cards. Options
      (implementor picks one or combines):
      - Add a small horizontal rule or "vs" divider element between the
        two cards when stacked (visible only below `sm:` breakpoint, hidden
        at `sm:` and above via `sm:hidden`).
      - Give the AIDE card a left accent border (`border-l-2` or
        `border-l-3` with a brighter color like `border-zinc-500`) that
        appears only at mobile, reinforcing "this is the one to pay
        attention to."
      - Optionally dim the Rules packs card further on mobile (e.g.,
        `opacity-80` below `sm:`) so the AIDE card pops by contrast.
- [x] Verify at 375px that the stacked cards communicate "this is bad /
      this is good" without needing side-by-side contrast.

Spec trace: Same as Step 4. The comparison must survive the mobile
single-column collapse. Playbook responsive render functions pattern:
when layouts diverge structurally between breakpoints, consider separate
render paths. Here the divergence is mild (visual treatment, not DOM
restructuring), so Tailwind responsive prefixes suffice.

