### Step 6: Strengthen the blockquote in HallucinationEvidence

File: `src/components/LandingPage/HallucinationEvidence/index.tsx`

- [x] Increase the blockquote left border from `border-l-2 border-zinc-700`
      to `border-l-2 border-zinc-500` (or `border-l-3 border-zinc-500`)
      so the quote is visually distinct from body text against the dark
      background. The quote is a key persuasion element per the spec —
      it cites peer-reviewed evidence against other tools' approach and
      must stand out.
- [x] Optionally add a subtle background tint to the blockquote container
      (e.g., `bg-zinc-900/30 rounded-r-lg p-5` wrapping the quote and
      its footer) to give it more visual weight. This is an implementor
      judgment call — the goal is emphasis without looking like marketing
      chrome.

Spec trace: Strategy beat 5 requires the Stanford HAI citation
"attributed verbatim" as evidence. The spec's persuasion structure places
this as the final piece of evidence before the closing CTA. The
blockquote must earn visual attention commensurate with its role.

