### Step 7: Give the footer install CTA visual weight

File: `src/components/shared/InstallFooter/index.tsx`

- [x] Wrap the `npx aidemd-mcp init` text in a styled code block or
      bordered container that matches the visual treatment of the hero's
      install command. Currently it is plain monospace text (`<code>`
      inside a `<p>`) which reads as an afterthought rather than a CTA.
      Options (implementor picks):
      - Wrap in a small bordered container (`rounded border
        border-zinc-700 bg-zinc-900/50 px-3 py-2 font-mono`) matching
        the design language of the HowItWorks brain card.
      - Use the same `CodeBlock` component the hero uses (import from
        `@/components/shared/CodeBlock`), but smaller / more compact if
        it supports a size variant.
- [x] Keep the "See full install instructions" link and the "Read the
      canonical spec" link exactly as they are. Only the command display
      changes.

Spec trace: The spec says the final install block is "identical to the
hero's install block" — it is the "safety-net CTA for visitors who
scrolled past the first one." The current implementation does not match
the hero's visual treatment. Full parity with the hero's CodeBlock is
ideal; a styled container is the minimum.

