### Step 8: Evaluate and reject — brand mark above the fold (Finding 8)

No file changes.

- [x] Acknowledge finding 8 (no brand/logo mark above the fold on mobile)
      and explicitly decline it. The spec states: "No persistent top
      navigation bar. The landing has no header that offers the visitor a
      way off the conversion path." And: undesired outcomes include "stock-
      icon feature grids" and anything that "reads as marketing-site
      chrome." A brand mark / wordmark above the hero is a header element
      that precedes the install command, pushing the install block below
      the fold on mobile — directly contradicting the spec's requirement
      that "a visitor reaches the install command before any scrolling."
      The h1 headline IS the identity anchor.

Spec trace: `outcomes.undesired` bullet 1 (no persistent top nav);
`outcomes.desired` bullet 1 (install command before scrolling); Strategy
"No persistent top navigation" paragraph.

